article.headline: Oklahoma 77, Colorado 61
article.story:
BOULDER, Colo. (AP) -- Leah Rush had 19 points and Laura Andrews
added 15 in Oklahoma's 77-61 win over Colorado Wednesday.

Rush also had three rebounds and one assist for the Sooners.

Andrews had three assists.

Jackie McFarland led in scoring for Colorado with 23 points and
seven rebounds.

At the half, Oklahoma led by eight after shooting 50 percent,
compared to Colorado's 38 percent. The Sooners shot 57 percent in
the second half to Colorado's 32 percent.
